{
  "bookId": "laozi-boshu",
  "num": 33,
  "title": "第三十三章（盡己）",
  "author": "老子",
  "authorId": "Laozi",
  "dynasty": "周",
  "era": "周",
  "genre": "prose",
  "verses": [
    {
      "text": "知人者 知也 自知者 明也"
    },
    {
      "text": "勝人者 有力也 自勝者 強也"
    },
    {
      "text": "知足者 富也 強行者 有志也"
    },
    {
      "text": "不失亓所者 久也 死不忘者 壽也"
    }
  ],
  "sections": {},
  "annotations": [],
  "layers": {
    "heshanggong": [
      {
        "id": "heshanggong-1",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 0,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 13
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "能知人好惡，是為智。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "heshanggong-2",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 0,
          "start": 7,
          "end": 8
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "人能自知賢與不肖，是為反聽無聲，內視無形，故為明也。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "heshanggong-3",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 1,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 1
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "能勝人者，不過以威力也。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "heshanggong-4",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 1,
          "start": 8,
          "end": 9
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "人能自勝己情欲，則天下無有能與己爭者，故為強也。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "heshanggong-5",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 2,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 1
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "人能知足，則長保福祿，故為富也。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "heshanggong-6",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 2,
          "start": 7,
          "end": 8
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "人能強力行善，則為有意於道，道亦有意於人。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "heshanggong-7",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 3,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 1
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "人能自節養，不失其所受天之精氣，則可以久。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "heshanggong-8",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 3,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 16
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "目不妄視，耳不妄聽，口不妄言，則無怨惡於天下，故長壽。",
        "source": "cham"
      }
    ],
    "wangbi": [
      {
        "id": "wangbi-1",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 0,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 13
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "知人者，智而已矣，未若自知者超智之上也。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "wangbi-2",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 1,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 14
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "勝人者，有力而已矣，未若自勝者無物以損其力，用其智於人，未若用其智於己也。用其力於人，未若用其力於己也。明用於己，則物無避焉，力用於己，則物無改焉。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "wangbi-3",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 2,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 1
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "知足自不失，故富也。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "wangbi-4",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 2,
          "start": 7,
          "end": 8
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "勤能行之，其志必獲，故曰强行者有志矣。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "wangbi-5",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 3,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 1
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "以明自察，量力而行，不失其所，必獲久長矣。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "wangbi-6",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 3,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 16
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "雖死而以為生之道不亡，乃得全其壽，身沒而道猶存，況身存而道不卒乎。",
        "source": "cham"
      }
    ]
  },
